15 SUMMARY
1166 This amendment replaces the bill, changes the title and adds an emergency preamble
1177 and emergency clause. It establishes maximum levels of assistance for housing assistance
1188 provided to or on behalf of a person residing in a certified recovery residence with
1199 occupancy of 26 or more beds, in an amount equal to 70% of the maximum levels of
2200 assistance for recovery residences with occupancy of 25 or fewer beds. It requires the
2211 Department of Health and Human Services to reimburse each municipality for housing
2222 assistance provided to or on behalf of a person residing in a certified recovery residence
2233 with occupancy of 26 or more beds, in an amount equal to 100% of housing assistance
2244 granted to that individual. It also directs the department to convene a stakeholder group of
2255 interested parties, including, but not limited to, individuals in recovery, operators of
2266 recovery residences, municipal officials and individuals representing the entity responsible
2277 for the certification of recovery residences in the State to review options for managing the
2288 costs of general assistance provided for residents of recovery residences, including possible
2299 expansion or creation of state-funded subsidy programs. The department must report its
3300 findings by February 1, 2026 to the Joint Standing Committee on Health and Human
3311 Services, and the committee has the authority to report out legislation related to the report.
